{"sections":{"main":{"type":"page-null","settings":{}},"image_banner_Xti3HP":{"type":"image-banner","blocks":{"heading_k4DxfR":{"type":"heading","settings":{"heading":"Meet Lisa","heading_size":"h1"}},"text_UAVUaJ":{"type":"text","settings":{"text":"Our growing story…","text_style":"body"}}},"block_order":["heading_k4DxfR","text_UAVUaJ"],"settings":{"image":"shopify:\/\/shop_images\/Media-1-scaled-2.jpg","custom_class":"lisa-story-hero","image_overlay_opacity":0,"image_height":"large","desktop_content_position":"middle-left","show_text_box":true,"desktop_content_alignment":"left","color_scheme":"","image_behavior":"none","mobile_content_alignment":"center","stack_images_on_mobile":true,"show_text_below":true}},"video_CHWhnk":{"type":"video","settings":{"heading":"","heading_size":"h1","enable_video_looping":false,"video_url":"https:\/\/vimeo.com\/212123540?dnt=1&app_id=122963","cover_image":"shopify:\/\/shop_images\/693558872-9e6e12325e7e6fff2e4d13f25d2e640a09f04881b2873853645f328c3395d549-d_1920x1080_175773dd-c1e7-40b2-aeb2-27bf8ae8e16d.jpg","description":"Lisa's Story","full_width":false,"color_scheme":"","padding_top":56,"padding_bottom":56}},"rich_text_WCY47d":{"type":"rich-text","blocks":{"heading_FdNpEw":{"type":"heading","settings":{"heading":"How it All Started…","hcolor":"#343434","heading_size":"h1"}},"text_E9bGP7":{"type":"text","settings":{"text":"<p>What began as a small cut-flower farm producing for local markets has grown into so much more. Lisa has become a leader in the cut-flower growing industry, author, accomplished speaker, teacher, and the owner of The Gardener’s Workshop.<\/p><p>It all began in 1998 because Lisa wanted to work in her garden as her career. At first, she sold her cut flowers to local florists and Colonial Williamsburg. The business soon grew to include florist throughout the Hampton Roads region, supermarkets, farmers markets, a members-only on-farm market, and a bouquet drop-off subscription service.<\/p>"}}},"block_order":["heading_FdNpEw","text_E9bGP7"],"settings":{"desktop_content_position":"center","text_class":"lisa-story-richtext","colorbg":"#ffffff","content_alignment":"left","color_scheme":"","full_width":false,"padding_top":40,"padding_bottom":52}},"image_with_text_MRXjif":{"type":"image-with-text","blocks":{"heading_tfJ3nt":{"type":"heading","settings":{"heading":"Planting a Seed","hfont":"Abhaya Libre","hcolor":"#343434","hsize":42,"heading_size":"h1"}},"text_qRnrFx":{"type":"text","settings":{"text":"<p>During this time Lisa began giving programs to garden clubs, master gardeners, commercial growers, and other groups. What became apparent is that people were eager for her simplified organic gardening methods and her greatest gift is sharing them.<\/p><p>The next natural step came when Lisa self-published <a href=\"https:\/\/thegardenersworkshop.com\/product\/book-download-the-easy-cut-flower-book\/\"><em><strong>The Easy Cut-Flower Garden<\/strong><\/em><\/a> in 2011 (only available digitally) a 100-page guide on how-to grow and harvest a small home cutting garden. Her program travels began to spread from Texas to Oregon to New York City and she went on to become published with <a href=\"https:\/\/thegardenersworkshop.com\/product\/book-cool-flowers-by-lisa-mason-ziegler\/\"><em><strong>Cool Flowers<\/strong><\/em><\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/thegardenersworkshop.com\/product\/vegetables-love-flowers-lisa-mason-ziegler\/\"><em><strong>Vegetables Love Flowers<\/strong><\/em><\/a>, and <a href=\"https:\/\/thegardenersworkshop.com\/product\/the-cut-flower-handbook\/\"><em><strong>The Cut Flower Handbook<\/strong><\/em><\/a><strong>.<\/strong> <\/p>","text_style":"body"}}},"block_order":["heading_tfJ3nt","text_qRnrFx"],"settings":{"image":"shopify:\/\/shop_images\/No-Till-2.jpg","image_radius":15,"custom_class":"lisa-story-col","colorbg":"#f7f7f7","column_width":"half","height":"adapt","desktop_image_width":"medium","layout":"image_first","desktop_content_position":"top","desktop_content_alignment":"left","content_layout":"no-overlap","section_color_scheme":"","color_scheme":"","image_behavior":"none","mobile_content_alignment":"left","padding_top":60,"padding_bottom":60}},"image_with_text_WD8aCJ":{"type":"image-with-text","blocks":{"heading_dFBQeG":{"type":"heading","settings":{"heading":"Laying Roots","hfont":"Abhaya Libre","hcolor":"#343434","hsize":42,"heading_size":"h1"}},"text_VWaBQw":{"type":"text","settings":{"text":"<p>In 2018 Lisa began creating online courses to share her programs and teachings. This style of teaching with it’s convenience, cost effectiveness, and lifetime unlimited access has proven to be another wonderful teaching tool. In 2019, embracing this technology even further and building an amazing in-house support administration team has allowed Lisa to produce online courses for others.<\/p><p>Lisa’s farm, known as <a href=\"https:\/\/thegardenersworkshop.com\/store\/\">The Gardener’s Workshop<\/a> is still a small market flower farm (100% outdoor field grown), and an online garden shop. The online store sells the same seeds, tools, supplies, and seed starting equipment that Lisa uses as well as signed copies of her books.  Lisa’s simple, instructive, and delightful gardening messages are reaching far beyond any expectation she ever had.<\/p><p>Lisa has been a member of the <a href=\"https:\/\/www.ascfg.org\/\">Association of Specialty Cut Flower Growers<\/a> since 2001 and served as the Mid-Atlantic Regional Director from 2016 to 2020. She is also a member of the <a href=\"https:\/\/gardencomm.org\/\">Garden Communicators International.<\/a><\/p>","text_style":"body"}}},"block_order":["heading_dFBQeG","text_VWaBQw"],"settings":{"image":"shopify:\/\/shop_images\/Books_2b61c262-79c3-496c-9c71-0b64d7a17041.jpg","image_radius":15,"custom_class":"lisa-story-col","colorbg":"#ffffff","column_width":"half","height":"adapt","desktop_image_width":"medium","layout":"text_first","desktop_content_position":"top","desktop_content_alignment":"left","content_layout":"no-overlap","section_color_scheme":"","color_scheme":"","image_behavior":"none","mobile_content_alignment":"left","padding_top":60,"padding_bottom":60}},"image_with_text_pLfweD":{"type":"image-with-text","blocks":{"heading_iQ7WbH":{"type":"heading","settings":{"heading":"Lisa Mason Ziegler’s Books and Online Courses:","hfont":"Abhaya Libre","hcolor":"#343434","hsize":42,"heading_size":"h1"}},"text_QpnjKT":{"type":"text","settings":{"text":"<ul><li><a href=\"https:\/\/thegardenersworkshop.com\/product\/flower-farming-school-online-with-lisa-mason-ziegler\/\"><em>Flower Farming School Online<\/em><\/a>, online course<\/li><li><a href=\"https:\/\/thegardenersworkshop.com\/product\/seed-starting-made-easy-online-course\/\"><em>Seed Starting Made Easy<\/em><\/a><em>,<\/em> online workshop<\/li><li><a href=\"https:\/\/thegardenersworkshop.com\/product\/the-easy-cut-flower-garden-online-course\/\"><em>The Easy Cut Flower Garden<\/em><\/a>, online workshop<\/li><li><a href=\"https:\/\/thegardenersworkshop.com\/product\/cool-flowers-beyond-the-book-for-flower-farming-online-course\/\"><em>Cool Flowers, Beyond the Book for Flower Farming<\/em><\/a>, online workshop<\/li><li><a href=\"https:\/\/thegardenersworkshop.com\/product\/book-cool-flowers-by-lisa-mason-ziegler\/\"><em>Cool Flowers<\/em><\/a>, book<\/li><li><a href=\"https:\/\/thegardenersworkshop.com\/product\/vegetables-love-flowers-lisa-mason-ziegler\/\"><em>Vegetables Love Flowers<\/em><\/a>, book<\/li><li><a href=\"https:\/\/thegardenersworkshop.com\/product\/the-cut-flower-handbook\/\"><em>The Cut Flower Handbook<\/em><\/a>, book<\/li><\/ul>","text_style":"body"}}},"block_order":["heading_iQ7WbH","text_QpnjKT"],"settings":{"image":"shopify:\/\/shop_images\/No-Till.jpg","image_radius":15,"custom_class":"lisa-story-col","colorbg":"#f7f7f7","column_width":"half","height":"adapt","desktop_image_width":"medium","layout":"image_first","desktop_content_position":"top","desktop_content_al